Defendant Dale R Berry in court with Attorney Nicholas Martinez.  Michele W. Hulgaard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for sentencing hearing.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Martinez makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #4:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS STRAIGHT TIME (CREDIT - 4 days)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No violent contact with: any family members
____Domestic Violence Counseling through a State Certified Batterers Intervention Program such as Alliance Counseling or Family Services of Waukesha;

COSTS:  $343.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted and remainder to be refunded to poster)

***Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.***
